{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52e763ce-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s2512"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2512"},"text":"§ 2512.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Disbursing officers; relief","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Whenever the United States Court of Federal Claims finds that any loss by a disbursing officer of the United States was without his fault or negligence, it shall render a judgment setting forth the amount thereof, and the Government Accountability Office shall allow the officer such amount as a credit in the settlement of his accounts.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52e763cf-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/978"},"text":"62 Stat. 978","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164/tI/s139/j/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164, title I, § 139(j)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-04-02"},"text":"Apr. 2, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/43"},"text":"96 Stat. 43","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/572/tIX/s902/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–572, title IX, § 902(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-29"},"text":"Oct. 29, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4516"},"text":"106 Stat. 4516","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/271/s8/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–271, § 8(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-07-07"},"text":"July 7, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/814"},"text":"118 Stat. 814","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52e763d0-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id52e763d1-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 253 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s147"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 147","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/1137"},"text":"36 Stat. 1137","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1921-06-10/ch18/s304"},"text":"June 10, 1921, ch. 18, § 304","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/24"},"text":"42 Stat. 24","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “paymaster, quartermaster, commissary of subsistence, or other” were omitted as covered by words “disbursing officer of the United States”. (See reviser’s note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s1496"},"text":"section 1496 of this title","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes were made in phraseology.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52e763d2-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id52e763d3-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/271"},"text"